We were a party of four (4) and made reservations earlier in the day with no problem. It was definitely fine dining. Tables and/or booths were comfortable, clean, and of high quality. We were seated by their large fish tank (floor to ceiling), which is very impressive. Menu selection was adequate for appetisers, soups/salads, entrees (sea food, beef, chicken, etc.), and deserts. They also had bar for a good variety of alcohol drinks.  We started off with the calamari appetiser (excellent!), then two of us had the lobster bisque and two had Cesar salads. For our entrees two of us had the prime rib and two had sea food (shrimp dishes) with asparagus as a side dish. To finish it off, the four of us share the molten chocolate cake desert with one having vanilla and the other with peanut butter ice cream. Coffee, expresso, tea, or after dinner drinks were offered. All of the food was prepared very well and the presentation was very appealing.  Our server was attentive and had a very pleasant personality (friendly, but not obtrusive). Food was delivered in a timely manner; however, we weren't rushed and was able to talk with each other, enjoying the evening. The Restaurant Manager and one of the Marketing Executives came by to see if we were enjoying our meal.  Overall we had a good meal and would have no problem going back again. Prices are as expected for this type of restaurant, a little high; however, you get what you pay for and felt that it was worth it. I gave it a 4 Star rating, which I would say it was a solid 4.5 (didn't have that option).

I ordered a far less expensive item which came out and half of it slid off the plate onto the floor as I moved it closer to the rest of the party...probably because our menus were in front of us still and the food server couldn’t put it in front of us. The hostess stood there and shoved bread into her mouth laughing saying... I saw that but I'm too hungry to care. It sat on the floor the whole time. Very unprofessional, mediocre food, awful service for high prices. You'd have better luck, service and attitude anywhere else. Go to Pappadeaux. I've tipped less than 15% once in my life.. this was the second. It's a shame because the aquarium behind the bar is amazing!! They need to have the service an attention to detail that their prices demand. Maybe the tables are a different story. Front of the house is a dog and pony show. The bartenders friend brought a pizza and everyone ran to get a piece. Is this high school hour or the first thing patrons see and bar patrons see at a supposed high end restaurant? Please hire people that care and are good at their jobs. I recommend that you don't go here if you expect a nice dinner with good service.

Wow!  Having dined all over the world it takes a lot to make me say Wow about an eating establishment,  The Chart House was a Wow experience that must be experienced to be understood. Our waiter was exceptional,  not good but great, he was helpful to our three younger diners who had never eaten in a 5 star restaurant without being condescending.  This was refreshing and made for an excellent dining experience. The food was worth the trip to Las Vegas, dare I say it made the trip to Vegas more special for this dining experience?  A resounding yes.  The shrimp was exquisite,  my steak cooked to perfection and, unlike most seafood steak establishments,  it had no fishy flavor added by the grill.  I highly recommend The Chart House for everyone to see what fine dining really is supposed to be.
